entries.title: Self-Help Hunger Program
entries.description: Volunteered directly with former Black Panther, Aunti Frances Moore. The Self-Help Hunger Program is run primarily by Frances. She provides a meal every Tuesday at Driver Plaza in North Oakland. My role was cleaning up and washing dishes. You can [learn more here](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LxG5bHKqpfo).

entries.title: Teacher, CodeNation
entries.description: Taught high school students how to code at [Emiliano Zapata Street Academy](http://oaklandstreetacademy.org). Code Nation equips students in under-resourced high schools with the skills, experiences, and connections that together create access to careers in technology. Note: Code Nation was formerly called ScriptEd.
